      "heading": "How to install Node.js in Ubuntu 18.04?",
      "date_time": "16-July-2018",
      "description": [
        "<p>The easiest way to download & install node.js from the console :</p>",
        "<pre><code>$ wget http://nodejs.org/dist/v8.13.4/node-v8.13.4-linux-x64.tar.gz\n$ sudo tar -C /usr/local --strip-components 1 -xzf node-v8.1.1-linux-x64.tar.gz</code></pre>",
        "<p>To check node.js installed, issue command:</p>",
        "<code>$ node -v</code>"
      ]
    }
  ]
}